This is fine however it would be good to remind readers not to call setState() unless the value has actually changed. Something like: 
```
final double newValue = double.tryParse(value);
if (newValue != null && newValue != _value) {
  setState(() {
    _value = myDouble.clamp(0, 100);
  });
}
```

